itemDescription: Baines [née Hunt], Sarah Jane [Jennie] (1866–1951), British suffragette and social reformer

wikipedia_page.main: Sarah Jane Baines (30 November 1866 – 20 February 1951) was a British-Australian feminist, suffragette and social reformer. She was the first suffragette to be tried by jury, and one of the first hunger strikers. She was known as 'Jennie Baines' in the suffragist movement.
